text: Kelly Catlin (November 3, 1995 â€“ March 7, 2019) was an American professional racing cyclist. She rode for UCI Women's Team. Catlin won gold medals in the women's team pursuit at the 2016, 2017 and 2018 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. She also won a silver medal in the same event at the 2016 Summer Olympics. Catlin was born in St. Paul, Minnesota. She was a triplet. Catlin killed herself on March 7, 2019 at Stanford University in Stanford, California. She was 23.
